@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction........@{ub}

@{b}***Notice*** This worms replacement sample pack has been finished since the
end of  March 96.  Obviously this has never been released and now I have
modem access I have decided to upload the package to a few BBS's.

A lot of the text within this guide may be out of date***@{ub}

This Worms replacement kit is a replacement set of samples for the game
worms (obvious to some).  Worms as you should know is the hit game of the
last few months from both Team 17 and Ocean.

One of the hilarious aspects of the game are the sampled voices of the worms
and how they react to events (i.e. How a worm shouts "MISSED" if you
incorrectly aim a shot).  Although the samples included with the game are
very funny I thought it would be fun to create some new samples for the
game.

With this in mind, @{"David and myself" link "Creators" 0} got all the necessary equipment together
(Sampler, Microphones etc..) and arranged similiar phrases that could be
substituted with the original ones included with worms.

I have had no access to what is happening in the land of worms (via the
Worms Web Site), but have recently bought the new CD version of CU Amiga
magazine and as you may know they included on the CD their own set of
samples for the game worms.  Although I find the samples funny, the samples
are mixed and matched.  I wanted our samples to be consistant with each
other like the original worms.  To keep the samples consistant I have spoken
all of the phrases in the set, but David will do all the samples for the
next set (when we get round to it).  As I have not accessed the Worms Web
page so I do not know of the sample sets that are said to be available on
the Web site (so it said in the readme on the CU Amiga CD).  Hopefully ours
are fit enough to go alongside these in quality.

If you have any suggestions on how we could make our set(s) better, or of
anything we have done wrong then please contact @{"us" link "Creators" 0}.  If we do more sets then
they can be improved with feedback.

UPDATED NOTE: Looking back on the sample set, I feel the spoken phrases are
comical, but the way in whch we produced the samples could of been done
better, and at a higher pitch.

