@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{b}Requirements........@{ub}

The requirements are the same as the game states.

To use these updated samples you will need an Amiga with 2MB chip mem. If
you are using a stock Amiga 1200 hundred then everything should be okay,
although older amigas with only 1MB chip memory (such as my mate Andy and
his A2000) will not be able to load the extra samples.@{b}

This sample set has been tested on both:@{ub}

- My Amiga 1200, 28mhz 68030, 2MB Chip, 2MB Fast, NO FPU, 80MB HD.

- My Sixthform's Amiga 1200, 68020, 2MB Chip, No Fast, NO FPU, 80MB HD.

- David's Amiga 600, 68000, 2MB Chip, No Fast, NO FPU, 120MB HD.

UPDATED NOTE: I have since bought an 8MB simm for my Viper Board.

                               @{"Contents" link "Main" 0}
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}Installation........@{ub}

Installation is simple, all you have to do is replace the samples in this
package with your original samples (it is advised that you replace to your
back-up copies of your original Worms).

For a comparison check, WORMS disk 2 (of which is full of samples) has
around 62k free disk space, when you replace the new sample set, the free
disk space will increase to around 78k.  So there is even less chance that
the game will not load if you have a bare minimum memory system (as in tests
a standard Amiga 1200, failed to load worms when large samples were used).

                               @{"Contents" link "Main" 0}
@endnode

